    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is mitigated by the analytical argument that the single quasi-static test condition represents the governing load case for the three specified QoIs. All quantitative validation metrics pass pre-specified acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%) for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. The overall credibility package is assessed as sufficient to support a Medium assurance level determination and regulatory submission.",
